Name: Corner Inn
Review Text: This place was exactly as expected, a small diner with a hometown feel that serves huge portions of amazing food.  Service was excellent and I would highly recommend this place

Name: Corner Inn
Review Text: Had a great little brunch with my bestie! The atmosphere is very homey and comfortable.  A nice little small town diner! I got the mess half order and a side of Hasbrouck and too much for me to finish.

Name: Corner Inn

Review Text: Good value, nice server, but only one server and it was busy, so she was running. She did good though. Pretty much just what I expected for a local family restaurant. Food was solid.

Name: Corner Inn
Review Text: This place is amazing, food is terrific, prices are in the ballpark, the service is outstanding, my brother had the farmers omelet, which was huge, I had what they call the bowl, which is biscuits and sausage gravy and two eggs, and toast, served in a bowl, you should be able to leave full, opens at 8am

Name: Corner Inn
Review Text: Hometown diner taste and service... food was amazing and way too much for any of us to finish...   Bring enough home to get another meal out it.. what a value. ‚Ä¶

Name: Corner Inn
Review Text: The Corner Inn is a can‚Äôt miss in Upper Sandusky and is hands down, the best breakfast spot in town. Delicious food and friendly staff will make for a great experience.

Name: Corner Inn
Review Text: The corner inn was a decent greasy spoon and local hang out.  The corn beef hash was a giant portion, heavy on the country fried potatoes.  Unfortunately, there is nothing special to make the diner stand out.

Name: Corner Inn
Review Text: This place is everything you would ever want in a dinner. Great staff, great food, great prices. They have everything you would expect in a place like this, but at considerable higher quality. Plenty of options. I would highly recommend you eat at the Corner Inn as often as possible.

Name: Corner Inn

Name: Corner Inn
Review Text: Small town restaurant set in a historic building in the heart of downtown. Pictures of Upper Sandusky's past adorn the walls. The menu has a lot of delicious options with good prices, and generous proportions. The service is friendly and fast. This is the regular spot for many locals during lunch and breakfast.
